All internal parts of the system need to comply with the radiopurity limits as well as guarantee a reliable long-term operation. A flexible hardware design (e.g. linearity checks of the PMTs) is needed, too, to provide the opportunity to adjust to further requirements in a future physics program of OSIRIS.
