				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\sim $$\end{document}7 ns (FWHM).

When driven at low intensities, the LED will provide a cross-check to the s.p.e.-based results of the fiber system (Sect. 3.5.1). In addition, the tunable intensity offers the chance to investigate the PMT response to higher p.e. occupancies. This is important since the average signal per PMT expected for OSIRIS is ≥\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
