				\begin{document}$$> 99{\%}$$\end{document}) and can be clearly identified by their high scintillation signal.

Expected performance In order to determine the required muon veto performance, an extensive set of cosmic muon events and their secondaries was simulated. Neutrons and radioisotopes from muon spallation in the LS can pose a correlated background to Bi–Po coincidence searches. Applying the corresponding selection cuts (Sect. 5.1.1), the expected rate of 214Bi\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
