Radon will emanate from the surfaces of all pipes and vessels coming into contact with LS on its way through the JUNO filling system. Moreover, gas leakage at valves and connections will add a low amount of radon from the ambient air. From estimates based on the system surfaces, emanation and leakage rates, the radon contamination expected during JUNO filling is on the order of 7–45 decays per day and ton, corresponding to an initial rate of n˙Rn(0)=130-830\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
