The OSIRIS facility serves as the last stage in the purification chain of JUNO, measuring the residual radioactivity of the LS before being injected into the JUNO Central Detector. OSIRIS will provide valuable information on the efficiency of the purification chain and issue a timely alert in case problems occur with the radiopurity of the LS. In this article, we have given a detailed overview of the technical design of the OSIRIS detector. It has been optimized to screen the LS to the required purity levels of U/Th within days for IBD-level (≤\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
